data.content:
Build succeeds with zero errors. Here's what changed:

```csharp
// Before (v2) — removed overload in v3
Assert.AreEqual(expected, actual);
Assert.AreNotEqual(a, b);
Assert.AreSame(obj, obj);

// After (v3) — explicit generic type parameter
Assert.AreEqual<object>(expected, actual);
Assert.AreNotEqual<object>(a, b);
Assert.AreSame<object>(obj, obj);
```

**Why this happens:** MSTest v3 removed the non-generic `Assert.AreEqual(object, object)` overload. The compiler now resolves to `Assert.AreEqual(string, string)` as the closest match, causing the CS1503 error. Adding `<object>` (or a more specific type like `<int>` if you know it) selects the generic overload instead.
